# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The McKenna-class battleship represents the absolute apex of human warship design. Displacing nearly two million tons, this leviathan served as the ultimate expression of Star League naval supremacy for over a century following its 2652 commissioning. Designed as the definitive capital warship of the Terran Hegemony, the McKenna was conceived to be so overwhelmingly powerful that no realistic combination of Successor State warships could hope to challenge one. Blue Nose Clipperships on Mars and the legendary Titan Yards at Terra shared production of approximately 280 vessels across 130 years, their hulls forming the backbone of the SLDF battle line. The revolutionary Cortex UltraBond hull technology, derived from the Farragut class's proven spaceframe, gave these enormous vessels their characteristic structural resilience, while banks of Kreuss heavy naval particle projectors provided the devastating broadside firepower that made the McKenna the most feared warship ever to patrol the space lanes of the Inner Sphere. Every numbered SLDF fleet counted at least one McKenna among its capital ships. Even centuries after the fall of the Star League, surviving vessels remained the most coveted prizes in any navy -- enduring symbols of absolute naval authority whose very presence could alter the course of interstellar conflict.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At 1,930,000 tons and 1,405 meters in length, the McKenna is the largest purpose-built warship class ever constructed by any Inner Sphere power. Its primary armament consists of forty-eight Kreuss XX Heavy Naval PPCs arranged in devastating broadside batteries -- twelve per broadside and twelve per aft flank -- capable of reducing any vessel to wreckage in a single coordinated salvo. This extraordinary energy battery is supplemented by ten Zeus-40 NAC/40 super-heavy naval autocannons and twelve Thunderbolt-55 NL55 naval lasers distributed across the nose, forward flanks, and aft arc, providing overlapping fields of fire in every engagement geometry. Six Maelstrom AR10 capital missile launchers loaded with mixed Barracuda, White Shark, and Killer Whale missiles provide flexible long-range striking power from the forward flanks and aft. The Ulston C5-A ferro-carbide armor provides exceptional protection, with the Star League variant mounting over 1,600 tons of plating. Heat management for this enormous weapons suite relies on 6,325 double heat sinks generating 12,650 points of effective dissipation, allowing sustained broadside fire without degradation. A lithium-fusion battery enables rapid successive jumps, providing strategic mobility unusual for a vessel of such mass. Six docking collars, bays for fifty aerospace fighters and sixteen small craft, and three gravity decks support the crew of nearly 760 in extended independent operations. The Clan refit introduced around 2851 added a mobile HPG for independent fleet communications while modestly adjusting the armor distribution and cargo capacity.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The SLS Terra served as the flagship of the entire SLDF Navy under Admiral Jonns Ezenwa, leading the prestigious First Fleet from the nerve center of Hegemony naval power. Her sister ships held comparably exalted positions: the SLS Camino Real as flagship of the Fourth Fleet, the SLS Duke of York heading the Fifth Fleet's famed 52nd Golden Fire Squadron alongside running mate the SLS Sevastopol, and the SLS Implacable leading the 182nd Line Squadron of the Eighteenth Fleet. The SLS Iona won Best WarShip at the 2668 Martial Olympiad, while the SLS McKenna earned the unique distinction of winning two consecutive competitions in 2696 and 2700 -- the only vessel in history to achieve such a feat. The Amaris Coup of December 2766 shattered this golden age. The SLS Star League was lost over Unity City on the first day while attempting to evacuate the First Lord. The SLS Enterprise, flagship of the First Fleet High Command Squadron under Deputy Commander Aaron DeChavilier, fought a sixteen-hour running engagement over Eastern Europe and destroyed the Republican flagship RWS Stefan Amaris before being overwhelmed. At the Battle of Lone Star in July 2772, Vice Admiral Noeki Giersson assumed fleet command from the SLS Sovereign Justice after the flagship Queribus was destroyed, rallying the remnants to eliminate the drone fleet. The SLS Caph escaped the initial coup to command a secret fleet operating from hidden bases during the Civil War.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The McKenna-class battleship emerged from a Terran Hegemony naval program initiated in the mid-twenty-seventh century to create the definitive SLDF capital warship. Blue Nose Clipperships on Mars received the primary construction contract, with the O'Neil Yards at the Titan orbital complex near Terra serving as a secondary production facility. The design team drew heavily on the Farragut class's proven Cortex UltraBond hull technology while dramatically scaling up the vessel's mass to nearly two million tons, creating a spaceframe capable of mounting the most powerful weapons battery ever fitted to a warship. The first McKenna entered service in 2652 and immediately established itself as the dominant capital ship in known space.</p><p>Production continued for over 130 years, with approximately 280 McKennas constructed across both yards. The class became synonymous with the Star League Defense Force itself -- no fleet review was complete without McKennas at its center, and no fleet commander considered their force adequate without at least one of these devastating battleships in the line of battle. The SLS Iona won Best WarShip at the 2668 Martial Olympiad, while the SLS McKenna achieved the unprecedented feat of winning two consecutive competitions in 2696 and 2700. Six vessels received the prestigious McKenna Command variant configuration, serving as supreme fleet flagships with enhanced command-and-control capabilities.</p><p>The Amaris Coup of December 2766 devastated the McKenna fleet. The SLS Star League was destroyed over Unity City on the first day while attempting to evacuate the First Lord. The SLS Enterprise fought a sixteen-hour engagement over Eastern Europe under Deputy Commander DeChavilier, destroying the Republican flagship before being overwhelmed. The Liberation of Terra and subsequent Civil War consumed dozens more. By the time Aleksandr Kerensky called for the Exodus in 2784, fewer than twenty McKennas remained operational.</p><p>Kerensky chose the SLS McKenna's Pride as his personal flagship for the journey into the Deep Periphery, cementing the vessel's already legendary status. Nicholas Kerensky continued the tradition, commanding from the McKenna's Pride during Operation KLONDIKE in 2821. When the Pentagon Worlds were secured, the surviving McKennas were distributed among the Clans as their most prestigious naval assets. Around 2851, the vessels received comprehensive refits incorporating lithium-fusion batteries and mobile HPGs, extending their operational relevance into a new era.</p><p>For over two centuries, McKennas served as the ultimate symbols of Clan naval power. The CSR James McKenna was Khan Stephen McKenna's flagship during KLONDIKE at Circe. The CWS Werewolf served Clan Wolf-in-Exile as flagship of the First Wolf Guardians. The CGS Lei Kung anchored Clan Goliath Scorpion's Einheriar Battlegroup. The CIH Cage's Pride led Clan Ice Hellion's Alpha Galaxy. Each vessel represented centuries of accumulated tradition and irreplaceable strategic capability.</p><p>The Jihad and Wars of Reaving destroyed most surviving McKennas in a cascade of catastrophic losses. The James McKenna fell at Ramora in 3069 when a terrorist DropShip detonated in its cargo bay, breaking the vessel's spine. The Werewolf was destroyed at Chara III in 3077 by nuclear SDS weapons during Operation SCOUR. The CCS Second Coming was captured by Society forces before being destroyed above Dagda by Clan Star Adder. The Cage's Pride was last seen under devastating fire at Vantaa after ordering catastrophic orbital strikes. The Sovereign Right conducted a brutal twenty-two-day bombardment at York that destroyed seventy-five percent of the population.</p><p>After Nicholas Kerensky's death, the McKenna's Pride had been maintained in orbit above Strana Mechty as a sacred memorial. During the Wars of Reaving, Clan Wolf operatives seized the vessel under Khan Vlad Ward's orders and concealed it within the Dark Nebula. In July 3147, saKhan Garner Kerensky recovered the legendary battleship, and the McKenna's Pride led the Wolf assault on Terra that established the ilClan -- the most famous warship in history carrying the legacy of Kerensky back to the world he had departed nearly four centuries earlier. As of 3151, the McKenna's Pride remains active above Terra, the last known McKenna-class battleship in existence and an enduring symbol of the naval supremacy that defined the Star League at its zenith.</p>
</history>

